news.title: H-RERA issues warrant to Shree Vardhman Infrahome for not handing over property
news.para: The court of the adjudicating officer, or AO, issued the warrant on February 7 after hearing the complaints of the allottee, HRERA said in a official statement.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso' residents hold candlelight march to mark one year of collapse
news.para: ​​Raising slogans like "Ghar Ke Badle Ghar" (a house for a house) and "Justice for Humanity, Justice for Chintels", the protesters marched to Deputy Commissioner (DC) Nishant Kumar Yadav's officer and submitted a memorandum to him listing their demands.

news.title: DTCP directs structural audit companies to meet RWAs of 15 societies
news.para: The four audit agencies — Bureau Vertias, TPC Technical Projects Consultants, Vintech Consultants, and NNC Design International — were drafted in by the district administration in August last year.

news.title: Canara Bank cuts lending rates by 15 basis points
news.para: The revised Repo Linked Lending Rate (RLLR) of the bank with effect from February 12, Canara Bank said in a regulatory filing on Friday.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: 13 residential-cum-commercial prime plots offered by Cidco
news.para: The bidder registration has already begun and e-tendering process will be completed by February 13. Subsequently, the e-auction will be conducted on February 15.

news.title: NCLT allows MHADA plea over its Patra Chawl land
news.para: The NCLT said, it appeared that Guruashish “has violated the joint development agreement (JDA) …’’ and MHADA was well within its rights to terminate the arrangement with the builder.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement's net profit up 17.73% in Q3 FY23
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,576.06 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 20.88 per cent from Rs 1,303.81 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: New developing areas to get over 3,500 LED streetlights in Nashik
news.para: Of the 3,500 LED streetlights, 40% will be installed in developing areas on the outskirts of Panchavati and Satpur divisions. The Nashik Municipal Corporation officials said that new residential areas are coming up on the outskirts of Nashik city.

news.title: Puravankara posts net profit of Rs 22.55 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Puravankara's consolidated total income stood at Rs 410.40 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 66.52 per cent from Rs 246.45 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Hong Kong's chief executive faces stern test over $3.4 billion bid to ease housing shortage
news.para: The global financial hub has long struggled with sky-high house prices, which have rocketed by 350% in the past two decades and created one of the widest wealth gaps in the world, making accommodation a serious social problem that Beijing is keen to see the city's leaders tackle.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso: No decision on payout for families who were forced to abandon homes
news.para: Tower D cannot be demolished before settling the claims of flat owners, for which a time of 60 days was defined when the order to raze the tower was issued.

news.title: Residents of Uruli & Phursungi divided over demerger from Pune civic body
news.para: While some citizens have welcomed the move, saying "better planning" of the areas will be possible after the demerger, others have threatened agitation if the areas are removed from the PMC limits. They described the demand for demerger as "politically motivated".

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body will cut UGD line for property tax defaulters
news.para: If defaulters continue to skip paying taxes, the HDMC will take measures to disconnect the UGD connection of their houses. From Thursday onwards, HDMC officials have started tough measures in the city to improve the revenue of the corporation.

news.title: India's GST Council will decide on cement tax rate after expert study
news.para: The fitment committee, which looks at the impact of rate changes, will meet to discuss and finalise its report on the lowering of a 28% GST rate on cement and submit it to the council, the chair, Vivek Johri, said.

news.title: Pune development body spots 124 illegal structures, demolishes two
news.para: Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) data revealed that the region had 8,177 illegal structures, for which notices have been issued. An official said 313 structures have so far been pulled down.
